logLevel.description: The log level. Possibles values are: TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN and ERROR

messageDescription.description: A more complete description of the message

TYPE_BACK_FORWARD.description: Navigation through a history traversal operation.

TYPE_NAVIGATE.description: Navigation started by clicking on a link, or entering the URL in the user agent's address bar, or form submission, or initializing through a script operation other than the ones used by TYPE_RELOAD and TYPE_BACK_FORWARD as listed below.

TYPE_RELOAD.description: Navigation through the reload operation or the location.reload() method.

TYPE_RESERVED.description: Any navigation types not defined by values above.

redirectCount.description: the number of redirects since the last non-redirect navigation under the current browsing context.

type.description: the type of the last non-redirect navigation in the current browsing context

connectEnd.description: time immediately after the user agent finishes establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the current document.

connectStart.description: time immediately before the user agent start establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the document.

domComplete.description: time recorded immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "complete".

domContentLoadedEventEnd.description: time recorded immediately after the DOMContentLoaded event completes.

domContentLoadedEventStart.description: time recorded immediately before the user agent fires the DOMContentLoaded event at the document.

domInteractive.description: time immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "interactive".

domLoading.description: time immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "loading".

domainLookupEnd.description: time immediately after the user agent finishes the domain name lookup for the current document.

domainLookupStart.description: time immediately before the user agent starts the domain name lookup for the current document.

fetchStart.description: time immediately before the user agent starts checking any relevant application caches.

loadEventEnd.description: time recorded immediately after the user agent completes the load event.

loadEventStart.description: time recorded immediately before the user agent fires the load event.

navigationStart.description: time immediately after the user agent finishes prompting to unload the previous document.

redirectEnd.description: time immediately after receiving the last byte of the response of the last redirect.

redirectStart.description: starting time of the fetch that initiates the redirect.

requestStart.description: time immediately before the user agent starts requesting the current document from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources.

responseEnd.description: time immediately after the user agent receives the last byte of the current document or immediately before the transport connection is closed, whichever comes first. The document here can be received either from the server, relevant application caches or from local resources

responseStart.description: time immediately after the user agent receives the first byte of the response from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources

secureConnectionStart.description: time immediately before the user agent starts the handshake process to secure the current connection.

unloadEventEnd.description: time immediately after the user agent finishes the unload event of the previous document.

unloadEventStart.description: time immediately before the user agent starts the unload event of the previous document.
